Bechamel Souce Recipe
Ingridients

 - Butter - 5 tablespoons
 - Flour (all-purpose) - 4 tablespoons
 - Milk - 4 cups
 - Salt - 2 teaspoons
 - Pepper - 1/4 teaspoon
 - Grated nuts - as desired

To make a Bechamel Souce follow these steps:

1. Heat the butter in a medium saucepan until melted
2. Add the flour and stir until smooth
3. Cook over a medium heat until the mixure turns a light sandy color
4. Add 1 and 1/2 cup of milk and stir well
5. Add the rest of the milk and stir constantly until very smooth
6. Remove from heat and let it cool
7. Enjoy white Bechamel Souce with your favourite meal

